  "stdout": "[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"@aikdna/writing\",\n    \"version\": \"0.7.2\",\n    \"judgment_version\": \"2026.05\",\n    \"status\": \"experimental\",\n    \"description\": \"Editorial writing judgment — diagnose whether content has a real argument, a cognitive hook, and evidence density. Not copy editing.\",\n    \"core_insight\": \"Most writing problems are structural and argument-level, not language-level.\",\n    \"keywords\": [\n      \"writing\",\n      \"editing\",\n      \"editorial\",\n      \"content\",\n      \"argument\",\n      \"judgment\"\n    ],\n    \"applies_when\": [\n      \"the user asks for content feedback, review, or 'why isn't this working'\",\n      \"the piece is structurally a discussion piece, blog post, essay, opinion article, or persuasion-oriented marketing copy\",\n      \"the user has the freedom to restructure (not just edit a fixed-form template)\",\n      \"the piece's purpose is to change a reader's belief, action, or framing\",\n      \"the piece competes for attention in a saturated channel (newsletter, blog, social feed)\",\n      \"the success metric is recall, sharing, or follow-up action (not lookup completion)\",\n      \"the reader has a choice whether to keep reading (search results, feed, inbox, social timeline)\",\n      \"the piece is competing with many alternatives for the reader's next 60 seconds\",\n      \"the user reports 'people aren't reading it' or 'engagement is low'\",\n      \"the piece makes claims the reader is being asked to accept or act on\",\n      \"the piece is argumentative, persuasive, analytical, or advisory\",\n      \"the author has access to specifics (cases, numbers, observations) even if they have not used them yet\"\n    ],\n    \"does_not_apply_when\": [\n      \"the task is copy editing for grammar, spelling, or compliance\",\n      \"the format is rigid (legal contracts, regulatory filings, technical reference docs)\",\n      \"the piece is informational-only by design (product specs, API docs, encyclopedia entries)\",\n      \"the user has explicitly asked only for line-level polishing\",\n      \"the piece is reference material the reader scans to look up an answer\",\n      \"the piece is neutral journalism whose role is to surface multiple positions, not advocate one\",\n      \"the piece is a status report whose value comes from clarity not persuasion\",\n      \"the reader has already committed (paid book, course, mandatory document)\",\n      \"the piece is a chapter or section inside a larger committed read\",\n      \"the genre conventions demand a slow start (academic abstract, legal preamble)\",\n      \"the piece is a brief opinion column or letter where the author's voice IS the evidence\",\n      \"the format constrains length severely (haiku, tweet, headline)\",\n      \"the piece is reflective or exploratory and signals uncertainty rather than asserting\"\n    ],\n    \"failure_risks\": [\n      \"Refusing to fix sentences when the user genuinely just wants smoother prose. Lecturing about structure when the user needs a 30-minute turnaround on existing content.\",\n      \"Pushing every neutral explainer toward becoming an opinion piece. Telling a documentation writer their API guide is 'forgettable' when memorability is not the goal.\",\n      \"Recommending a punchy opening for a long-form whitepaper where the audience expects a measured executive summary. Diagnosing a hook problem when the real issue is the piece is buried in an unindexed location.\",\n      \"Demanding citations in casual personal essays. Killing voice in short-form posts by insisting every line has a statistic. Refusing to help when the author genuinely is writing speculation.\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n",
